`RequestTracing()` middleware (line 94) which extracts trace context from incoming requests at line 103 using `otel.GetTextMapPropagator().Extract(req.Context(), propagation.HeaderCarrier(req.Header))`. This is the main entry point for trace propagation into Grafana.\n\n**Trace Context Extraction from Headers:** Multiple files handle extraction scenarios:\n- `pkg/apiserver/endpoints/filters/tracing_log.go` - `spanContextFromHeaders()` (line 37) extracts trace context using both standard W3C headers and custom Grafana-specific headers\n- `pkg/apiserver/endpoints/filters/upstream_trace_link.go` - `WithExtractUpstreamTraceLink()` (line 14) extracts from custom headers and creates span links\n- `pkg/apiserver/endpoints/filters/jaeger_tracing.go` - `WithExtractJaegerTrace()` (line 11) extracts Jaeger trace context from headers using the Jaeger propagator\n\n**gRPC Server-Side:** `pkg/services/grpcserver/interceptors/tracing.go` - `TracingStreamInterceptor()` (line 15) extracts trace context from gRPC metadata at line 19: `ctx = otel.GetTextMapPropagator().Extract(ctx, propagation.HeaderCarrier(md))`\n\n**HTTP Client-Side (Outgoing):** `pkg/infra/httpclient/httpclientprovider/tracing_middleware.go` - `TracingMiddleware()` (line 25) creates a middleware that injects trace context into outgoing requests at line 37: `tracer.Inject(ctx, req.Header, span)`\n\n**SMTP Integration:** `pkg/services/notifications/smtp.go` (line 116) injects trace context into email headers: `otel.GetTextMapPropagator().Inject(ctx, gomailHeaderCarrier{m})`\n\n### Prometheus (prometheus/prometheus)\n\n**Tracing Manager:** `tracing/tracing.go` implements the `Manager` type that configures global trace context propagation. In the `Run()` method (line 61), it sets the global TextMapPropagator: `otel.SetTextMapPropagator(propagation.TraceContext{})` (line 62). This uses the standard W3C Trace Context format.\n\n**HTTP Client-Side (Outgoing):** `storage/remote/client.go` - Both `NewReadClient()` (line 151) and `NewWriteClient()` (line 183) use `otelhttp.NewTransport()` to wrap the HTTP client transport. For write clients, this is explicitly shown at lines 223-227 where `otelhttp.NewTransport()` is called with HTTP trace options, enabling automatic trace context injection into remote write requests.\n\n### Pattern Summary\n\nAll three services follow the same OpenTelemetry propagation pattern:\n1. **Configuration:** Set global TextMapPropagator using `otel.SetTextMapPropagator()` with composite propagators\n2. **Server-side (Extract):** Use `TextMapPropagator.Extract(ctx, carrier)` to extract from request headers (`propagation.HeaderCarrier`)\n3. **Client-side (Inject):** Use `TextMapPropagator.Inject(ctx, carrier)` to inject into outgoing request headers\n4. **Instrumentation:** Use otelhttp/otelgrpc libraries that handle propagation automatically\n\nThe implementation supports fallback mechanisms (e.g., Grafana's custom header handling) and can compose multiple propagator formats (W3C Trace Context + Baggage + Jaeger) to ensure compatibility across different tracing backends."
}
